  "prompt": "What hand drawn anime is out there?",
  "response": "Hand-drawn anime, often referred to as traditional animation, involves creating each frame by hand rather than relying solely on digital tools like CGI. While many modern anime incorporate digital techniques to enhance efficiency and visual effects, a significant number still retain the charm and artistry of hand-drawn animation. Here are some notable hand-drawn anime films and series:\n\n### **Studio Ghibli Films**\nStudio Ghibli is renowned for its commitment to traditional hand-drawn animation, creating some of the most beloved anime films of all time.\n- **Spirited Away (2001)** \u2013 Directed by Hayao Miyazaki, this film won an Academy Award for Best Animated Feature and is celebrated for its stunning visuals and storytelling.\n- **My Neighbor Totoro (1988)** \u2013 A heartwarming tale of two sisters and their adventures with magical creatures.\n- **Princess Mononoke (1997)** \u2013 An epic historical fantasy that explores the conflict between humans and nature.\n- **Howl's Moving Castle (2004)** \u2013 A visually mesmerizing story blending magic and romance.\n\n### **Makoto Shinkai Films**\nWhile incorporating digital elements, Makoto Shinkai's works retain a strong foundation in hand-drawn artistry.\n- **Your Name (2016)** \u2013 A box-office hit known for its breathtaking animation and emotional narrative.\n- **Weathering with You (2019)** \u2013 A visually stunning film exploring themes of love and climate.\n- **5 Centimeters per Second (2007)** \u2013 A poignant story about love and distance, praised for its detailed art.\n\n### **Other Notable Hand-Drawn Anime Films and Series**\n- **A Silent Voice (2016)** \u2013 A touching story addressing bullying, disability, and redemption, with beautiful hand-drawn animation.\n- **The Girl Who Leapt Through Time (2006)** \u2013 A charming film blending romance and time travel with traditional animation.\n- **Princess Tutu (2002\u20132003)** \u2013 A unique series combining fairy tale elements with intricate hand-drawn sequences.\n- **Violet Evergarden (2018\u20132020)** \u2013 Although it uses digital techniques, the series maintains a strong hand-drawn aesthetic, especially in character designs and backgrounds.\n- **Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba (2019\u2013 )** \u2013 Features a mix of traditional and digital animation, renowned for its fluid fight scenes and detailed artwork.\n- **Mob Psycho 100 (2016\u20132019)** \u2013 Combines hand-drawn characters with vibrant, dynamic backgrounds and effects.\n\n### **Classic Hand-Drawn Anime**\n- **Neon Genesis Evangelion (1995\u20131996)** \u2013 A groundbreaking series that combines traditional animation with deep psychological themes.\n- **Cowboy Bebop (1998\u20131999)** \u2013 Known for its stylish animation and blend of genres, maintaining a hand-drawn look throughout.\n- **Samurai Champloo (2004\u20132005)** \u2013 A unique mix of traditional samurai themes with hip-hop influences, all depicted through hand-drawn animation.\n\n### **Modern Works Emphasizing Hand-Drawn Aesthetics**\nWhile many studios use digital tools, certain series strive to preserve a hand-drawn feel:\n- **Keep Your Hands Off Eizouken! (2020)** \u2013 Celebrates the art of animation with a vibrant, hand-drawn style.\n- **The Tale of the Princess Kaguya (2013)** \u2013 Although a Studio Ghibli film, it deserves special mention for its unique, brushstroke-like hand-drawn aesthetic inspired by traditional Japanese art.\n\n### **Independent and Niche Titles**\n- **Shouwa Genroku Rakugo Shinjuu (2016\u20132017)** \u2013 A beautifully animated series focusing on the art of rakugo storytelling.\n- **Mushishi (2005\u20132006, 2014)** \u2013 Known for its serene and detailed hand-drawn backgrounds that complement its mystical themes.\n\n### **Why Hand-Drawn Anime Matters**\nHand-drawn animation brings a unique warmth and personal touch to anime, allowing for intricate details and expressive characters that resonate deeply with audiences. While digital animation offers numerous advantages in terms of efficiency and effects, many creators and studios continue to value the artistry and craftsmanship inherent in traditional hand-drawn techniques.\n\n### **Where to Watch**\nMost of these titles are available on popular streaming platforms such as:\n- **Netflix**\n- **Crunchyroll**\n- **Funimation**\n- **Hulu**\n- **Amazon Prime Video**\n- **HBO Max** (for Studio Ghibli films)\n\n### **Conclusion**\nHand-drawn anime remains a vital and cherished part of the anime industry, celebrated for its artistic depth and emotional resonance. Whether you're a longtime fan or new to anime, exploring these hand-drawn titles can offer a rich and rewarding viewing experience.\n\nIf you're interested in specific recommendations or more information about a particular series or film, feel free to ask!",
